quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,"They are not (all) equal. Of the population of the Book (Or: Family of the Book; i.e., the Jews and Christians) is an upright nation (who) recite the signs (i.e., verses) of Allah at various times of the night as they prostrate themselves (to Him)"
  3,114,"They believe in Allah and the Last Day, and command beneficence, and forbid maleficence, and vie swiftly in charitable deeds; and those are of the righteous"
  3,115,"And whatever charity they perform, (then) they will never be disavowed (the reward of it), and Allah is Ever-Knowing of the pious"
  3,116,"Surely the ones who have disbelieved, their riches will never avail them, neither their children, anything against Allah; and those are the companions (i.e., the inhabitants) of the Fire, and they are therein eternally (abiding)"
  3,117,"The likeness of whatever they expend in this present life (Literally: the lowly \"life\", i.e., the life of this world) is as the likeness of a wind wherein there is clamoring cold that afflicted the tillage of a people who did injustice to themselves, and so it did cause it to perish. And in no way did Allah do any injustice to them but they did injustice to themselves"
  3,118,"O you who have believed, do not take to yourselves retainers, apart from your (people); they spare nothing to (cause) confusion to you; they would like to (bring you) whatever distresses you. Abhorrence has already been displayed of their mouths, and whatever their breasts conceal is (still) greater. We have already made evident to you the signs, in case you consider"
  3,119,"Now, you are those ones who love them, and they do not love you, and you believe in the Book, all of it. And when they meet you, they say, \"We have believed.\" And when they go away in private, they bite at you their finger-tips in rage. Say, \"Die in your rage; surely Allah is Ever-Knowing of the inmost (thoughts) in the breasts \" (Literally: what the breasts own)"
  3,120,"In case a fair (reward) touches you, (i.e. the believers) it vexes them; and in case an odious (disadvantage) afflicts you, they exult with it. And in case you are patient and pious, their plotting will harm you nothing. Surely Allah is Supremely Encompassing of whatever they do"
  3,121,"And (remember) as you went forth early from your family to locate the believers in their positions (Literally: seats) for fighting; (The reference is to the Battle of' Uhud) and Allah is Ever-Hearing, Ever-Knowing"
  3,122,"(Remember) as two sections of you were about to be disheartened, and Allah is their Ever- Patronizing Patron; and on Allah let the believers then put their trust"
  3,123,"And indeed Allah readily granted you victory at Badr, and you were humble; so be pious to Allah, that possibly you would thank (Him)"
  3,124,"As you said to the believers, \"Is it never sufficient for you that your Lord should supply you with three thousand of the Angels sent down (upon you)"
  3,125,"Yes indeed, in case you are patient and pious, and (the enemy) comes up (against) you instantly, (Literally: this instant of theirs) your Lord will supply you with five thousand of the Angels, markedly swooping"
  3,126,"And in no way has Allah made (this supply) except as good tidings to you and that thereby your hearts may be composed; and in no way does victory (come) except from the Providence of Allah, The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Wise"
  3,127,"That He may cut off a fringe of the ones who have disbelieved or suppress them, so they would turn over disappointed"
  3,128,"You have nothing to do concerning the Command, (i.e. My Command) whether He relents towards them or torments them, as surely they are unjust"
  3,129,"And to Allah (belongs) whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth. He forgives whomever He decides and torments whomever He decides; and Allah is Ever-Forgiving, Ever-Merciful"
  3,130,"O you who have believed, do not eat riba, (i.e., usury; interest and other unlawful gains) doubled (and) redoubled, and be pious to Allah that possibly you would prosper"
  3,131,And protect yourselves from the Fire that is prepared for the disbelievers
  3,132,And obey Allah and the Messenger that possibly you would be granted mercy